spanishExample: ¡No vuelvan a hacer eso! Esto no es real.
englishTranslation: (Plural) Don’t do that again! This isn’t real.

spanishExample: ¡Vuelve a la escuela! No te hemos vuelto a ver.
englishTranslation: Come back to school! We haven’t seen you again.

spanishExample: Me he sentido como un santo, pero ahora tengo que volver.
englishTranslation: I have felt like a saint, but now I have to go back.

spanishExample: No he vuelto a ver a la dama en un tiempo.
englishTranslation: I haven’t seen the lady again in a while.

spanishExample: No quiero que ella vuelva, pero quiero que tú vuelvas.
englishTranslation: I don’t want her to come back, but I want you to come back.

spanishExample: No quiero que volvamos al lugar secreto.
englishTranslation: I don’t want us to go back to the secret place.

spanishExample: No volverán a hablar con él sobre los demonios.
englishTranslation: They won’t talk to him about the demons again.

spanishExample: No vuelva a menos que diga que lo siente.
englishTranslation: (Formal) Don’t come back unless you say you’re sorry.

spanishExample: No vuelvas a hacer eso o ella volverá a estar triste.
englishTranslation: Don’t do that again or she will be sad again.

spanishExample: No vuelve a hablar con ella.
englishTranslation: He isn’t talking to her again.

spanishExample: Nos volveremos a ver cuando ellos vuelvan.
englishTranslation: We’ll see each other again when they come back.

spanishExample: Quiero que vuelva a su casa.
englishTranslation: I want her to come back to her house.

spanishExample: Siempre volvemos a casa temprano.
englishTranslation: We always come back home early.

spanishExample: Siempre vuelve a las cuatro, pero ayer volvió a las tres.
englishTranslation: He always comes back at four, but yesterday he came back at three.

spanishExample: Tienes que volver; si vuelves, todo estará bien.
englishTranslation: You have to go back; if you go back, everything will be fine.

spanishExample: Volveré a pensar en mi futura esposa.
englishTranslation: I will think about my future wife again.

spanishExample: Volvieron a hablar con ella y ella quiere que volvamos.
englishTranslation: They spoke with her again, and she wants us to come back.

spanishExample: Volvimos a sentir lo mismo; ¿lo sientes?
englishTranslation: We felt the same thing again; do you feel it?

spanishExample: Volviste porque yo volví.
englishTranslation: You came back because I came back.

spanishExample: Vuelven a hablar del diablo.
englishTranslation: They talk about the devil again.

spanishExample: Vuelvo al hospital.
englishTranslation: I’m going back to the hospital.
